ace. Make it tight for formality, or ruffle it up a bit to show a little bit of character and playfulness, this item cradling the neck works great as a gift idea for that special, if not a tad eccentric, someone. Always remember, it used to be that sissies were mistaken for gentlemen, now it is gentlemen that are mistaken for sissies, but I say nay. So gents and dames: don’t be shy, sport a bow tie!</div>\n<table class=\"tr-caption-container\" style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: right;\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"center\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><a style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_EkC9jzJ0sAY/TP_FwUvOV0I/AAAAAAAAACE/OKhz-c7y5T8/s1600/joyce+boy.jpg\"><img src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_EkC9jzJ0sAY/TP_FwUvOV0I/AAAAAAAAACE/OKhz-c7y5T8/s1600/joyce+boy.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tr-caption\" style=\"text-align: center;\">I am a motherfucker.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>','The Bow Tie: Retaking its Sartorial Crown.','','inherit','open','open','','48-autosave','','','2011-02-07 13:38:24','2011-02-07 13:38:24','',48,'http://modernaddendum.com/?p=69',0,'revision','',0),(111,2,'2011-02-18 19:28:11','2011-02-18 19:28:11','People try to live safely: they avoid danger, hazards and any other misnomers that prone the body towards discombobulation. Fortunately, the two-man outfit Youvultures comes crashing, obliterating superstructures with their first release, the EP <em>WWYVD?</em>\r\n\r\nThe title tracks opens up with a mock fanfare before whipping out its machine-gun fuzzed-out bass slams and back breaking beats spread across everywhere. Seconds into the track it freezes with a choir yelps before resuming its rolling-thunder groove. The opener assures the doubtful, and probably frightened, listeners that the remaining rumpus does not shy away from this aesthetic: an ear-annihilating, relentless clusterfuck. “HYV” is an upward scaling distorted chromatic gear-shift drive-by with vacuum-sealed ultra-tight drumming before it begins collapsing on itself with a flood of modulated noises and half-time percussion extracted from a Mars landscape.\r\n\r\n“Carne Trémula’s” intro sound clip urges the listener to the proverbial past time of “fucking your own face” but the band opts to facilitate the process with this ripper before segueing into the pseudo-dance floor stomper “La Playa” , á la Les Rallizes Denudés ,which will force the limbs of brain-melted wasteoids into flux while the closer “La Porno” phases in and out with moaning-cum-feedback laden devastating sonic raunchiness.\r\n\r\nThe band juggles between hyper-constructed angular runs, inspired by their high-school algebra classes, and full-blown noise warbles. Youvultures might have The Locust-inspired presentation but their execution beckons to a wider audience.\r\n\r\nProduction is sleek and the duo set-up helps create a balance in equalization: drums don’t tread on the bass and the bass has enough mid-range punch to cut through production. The cornucopia of Moog-like soundscapes is not cluttered or muddied under the instruments and ring out with clarity and nefariousness.  The soundclip intros are an interesting addition, demonstrating craftsmanship in the record: it’s not just a loose amalgamation of singles and whatnot but more of a solid cultural artifact with a narrative that gives it cohesion.\r\n\r\nThe only discrepancy is the record’s length, clocking it at a little less than 10 minutes, something which might blueball listeners craving-mad for more. It seems too early (and too short) to establish Youvultures as a hard-hitting headliner but the brutality of <em>WWYVD?, </em>drawing virgins into its vortex of sonic sacrifice,  is certainly numbing skulls and everyone should stone their gray matter with this ripper.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://youvultures.bandcamp.com/album/wwyvd-ep\">Stream it baby! </a>','Sonic slutiness and  Youvulture\'s \"WWYVD?\"','','publish','open','open','','a-quick-one-youvultures-wwyvd','','','2011-02-18 21:44:55','2011-02-18 21:44:55','',0,'http://modernaddendum.com/?p=111',0,'post','',2),(72,2,'2011-02-12 18:42:51','2011-02-12 18:42:51','Scene: you waltz into your locally owned bookstore in search for a text that might pique your interest and find that a couple of your favorite local bands have released their latest sonic concoction on luscious slabs of glassy black paste and silvery-smooth CDs. When you get home, you read on the internet that yet another local group has cut a record and you can download it for free. What’s going on? Groups are currently spewing audio warble through every viable medium, both inside and outside the island. Digital data or concrete compact discs and records?\r\n\r\nThe contemporary debate has limited its spectrum of vision to quarrelling and squabbling over whether or not vinyl format is making is becoming the new “in” thing (and subsequently taking the money out of most of us audiophiles) but the true dilemma, the bona fide question, is which medium is going to trump at the end.\r\n\r\nThe vinyl boom of the last 5 years has certainly changed the playing field radically introducing newcomers to the fascinating, exhilarating (not to mention expensive) obsessive-compulsive habit of record collecting but also revamping the compact-disc market in its golliwog stomp to its rightful place in the music industry (Kanye West’s My Beautiful Dark Twisted Fantasy blasting a whopping 465,000 unit sale in both vinyl and CD format). Ironically, digital exclusives have simultaneously stomped down the door, scrounging for a piece of the pie (viz. Of Montreal’s digital box set) and on-line only purchases have steeped to market scales where eagles dare to fly ( iTunes reaching the 10 billion dollar mark last year, that’s roughly around 46 tracks being purchased every second.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_80\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\" caption=\"This is a caption\"]<a href=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/spooky2.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-80\" title=\"spooky\" src=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/spooky2-300x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a></dt> </dl></div>\r\nPerhaps the ethos surrounding physical release is what establishes the item as a fetishistic ideal that has allowed it to preserver. It is the ultimate synthesis between the graphic display of its Technicolor casing and its contained warble, awaiting to rearrange recalcitrant air molecules. Physical releases have become the emblems of preserving the rock n’ roll canon and local bands have not shied away from manufacturing fore mentioned cultural artifacts. The latest releases from Campo-Formio (“Spooky Fools”and  Tach Dé (self-titled) have proven that there are still performing artists who uphold such an agenda, devoting time and effort to crafting a piece of work that goes further than its “raison d’être”, that is, it’s not merely the transportation of music from the artist to its acolyte, but a holistic endeavor, an enterprise of manufacturing bona fide art in this day and age ( “Spooky Fools” proved to be one of 2010’s most assiduously calculated and beautifully rendered productions.)\r\n<div class=\"mceTemp\"><dl id=\"attachment_75\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\" style=\"width: 480px;\"><dt class=\"wp-caption-dt\"><a href=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/campo.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-75\" title=\"campo\" src=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/campo.jpg\" alt=\"Alternate\" width=\"470\" height=\"269\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe hurdles of this format are embodied as agents against of accessibility: location and cost. The metropolitan system opens spaces to have the music of homegrown groups exposed to an ampler audience at the cost of limiting the availability to the denizens of the area and the toughening times mean a pretty penny for the price of such marvelous cultural artifacts.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_74\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"275\" caption=\" \"]<a href=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/tach.de_.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-74  \" title=\"tach.de\" src=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/tach.de_-275x300.jpg\" alt=\"Tach De\" width=\"275\" height=\"300\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis is then where digital downloads overtake: skimming printing and packaging prices (also having the best of both worlds still preserving all the art from its counterpart) and putting their product in the information superhighway almost guaranteeing a solid listen to anyone with internet access (granted they know how to use it, apologies to “The Jersey Shore” cast.). 2010 saw the marvelous, and digital-only, releases of Fantasmes (“Sidtracked”) and Similar ( self-titled EP)which demonstrates how some are taking advantage of the ever-evolving contemporary communications. Yet a modern reaction to the excess of accessibility is skepticism: pr\r\n\r\noblems with “quality control” (any band could upload their rattle and hum) and the sometimes the deviation into shoddy artwork and assembly. The main difficulty is that local releases have limited their digital packaging to rudimentary aspects such as cover sleeve and maybe lyrics and have yet to expand features (much like Radiohead did their 2009 free downloadable single “These AreMy Twisted Words” which incorporated fascinating ASCII art panels among other tidbits.) One should not decry that bands with digital releases are merely partaking in shabby productions, these groups are merely accommodating to the times.\r\n\r\nBut at the gist of it, since audio quality is a creative and economic control which the band <a href=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/fantasmes.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-73 alignright\" title=\"fantasmes\" src=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/fantasmes-300x277.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"277\" /></a>is solely responsible for, concrete format holds scissor that will the unmake the Gordian knot. The metaphysics of the experience are fundamental for appreciation: the act of unwrapping, popping it in and listening are held by the narrative structure of creating an immersive experience that  is a dialectic between the listener, the object of aesthetic knowledge which  is the “real” record (whether it be 12’’ or 12 cm) , and the band itself, something which doesn’t necessarily translate to listening music on the go (iPod or in a car) or engaging it mechanically via a person to computer listening session (not “dissing” this experience of course.)\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/similar.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-77 alignleft\" title=\"similar\" src=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/similar-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIt would be interesting to see a more inclusive and expansive record/data experience, such as online exclusive added bonuses á la Director’s Cut,  beside the digital download bonus option which is a staple for both CD and vinyl releases nowadays (the 7’’ “Spooky Fools” being one of those). Though concrete format seems to be going down in sales (thanks to internet piracy which none of us listeners partake, ahem) and everything now is digested in itty-bitty data fun-sized chunks, people will probably continue getting their literal hands on their favorite tracks for a while. The times have certainly changed (as well as the rules of the game) it’s reassuring that there are still dedicated enough aural art devotees hanging around, and they are making it their task that music gets out, ensuring that people have options like they deserve to.\r\n\r\nOriginally published Feb. 12, 2010 in the <a href=\"http://www.prdailysun.com/index.php?page=news.article&amp;id=1297525196\" target=\"_blank\">Puerto Rico Daily Sun</a>','Local music\'s contemporary conundrum: digital vs. physical format. ','','publish','open','open','','local-musics-contemporary-conundrum-digital-vs-physical-format','','','2011-02-13 11:34:56','2011-02-13 11:34:56','',0,'http://modernaddendum.com/?p=72',0,'post','',0),(73,2,'2011-02-11 18:04:16','2011-02-11 18:04:16','','fantasmes','Fantasmes\' \"Sidetracked\" (Digital Download)','inherit','open','open','','fantasmes','','','2011-02-11 18:04:16','2011-02-11 18:04:16','',72,'http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/fantasmes.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(74,2,'2011-02-11 18:04:33','2011-02-11 18:04:33','','tach.de','','inherit','open','open','','tach-de','','','2011-02-11 18:04:33','2011-02-11 18:04:33','',72,'http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/tach.de_.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(75,2,'2011-02-11 18:05:00','2011-02-11 18:05:00','Description','campo','This is a caption','inherit','open','open','','campo','','','2011-02-11 18:05:00','2011-02-11 18:05:00','',72,'http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/campo.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(76,2,'2011-02-11 18:05:31','2011-02-11 18:05:31','','spooky','','inherit','open','open','','spooky-2','','','2011-02-11 18:05:31','2011-02-11 18:05:31','',72,'http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/spooky.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(77,2,'2011-02-11 18:08:35','2011-02-11 18:08:35','','similar','Similar EP (Digital Download) ','inherit','open','open','','similar','','','2011-02-11 18:08:35','2011-02-11 18:08:35','',72,'http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/similar.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(78,2,'2011-02-11 18:09:20','2011-02-11 18:09:20','Scene: you waltz into your locally owned bookstore in search for a text that might pique your interest and find that a couple of your favorite local bands have released their latest sonic concoction on luscious slabs of 