.   With modern rock journalism squabbling over whether or not the newest band is lo-fi enough to be garnered the ideological “garage” tag, Los Vigilantes is a welcome act that combines the best of all possible worlds, because in the end, it all sounds like good rock n’ roll to me.\r\n\r\nLos Vigilantes will be releasing their self-titled record this Thursday at Nuestro Son in Old San Juan alongside Las Ardillas. The album will be available in both CD and Vinyl format.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/17972132?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"400\" height=\"225\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe><p><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/17972132\">LOS VIGILANTES - VEN VAMOS</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/user2379619\">PURO VICIO</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Vigis.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-235\" title=\"Vigis\" src=\"http://modernaddendum.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Vigis.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"576\" height=\"384\" /></a>','Los Vigilantes and their non-stop joy ride into the outlawed heart of rock n’ roll','Local greasers all lubed up with their latest hip-shaking extravaganza. ','inherit','open','open','','234-revision-6','','','2011-07-06 00:41:39','2011-07-06 00:41:39','',234,'http://modernaddendum.com/2011/07/234-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(244,2,'2011-07-06 00:42:13','2011-07-06 00:42:13','The needle drops and the opening riff of “Ven, Vamos” starts jangling, introducing a familiar melody from some brighter, half-remembered life that buoys with an uncomplicated sense of fun, adventure, youth and a dash of frustration and melancholy. Such is the ethos and sound of local greasers Los Vigilantes’ self-titled, full-length debut on Slovenly records. Already experienced in the vinyl arts with thesir “Mi Mami Dijo/Que Mal” ’45 single and a superb cover of the Rolling Stones’ “Paint it Black” on Norton records, the four-man ensemb